<span id="freeTextContainer9884016225438555814">&quot;Solacers&quot; is a big look into a largely unknown culture from the point of view of one of the unprivileged inside it. I was touched by the matter of fact way in which the story was told, not only because of the bad times our young protagonist goes through, but also because of the way in which he decides to thank every single person that helped him along the way.<br/><br/>The writing itself would have benefited from a more exhaustive editing work. Even though the language is very good, the long sentences an</span>
  <span id="freeText9884016225438555814" style="display:none">"Solacers" is a big look into a largely unknown culture from the point of view of one of the unprivileged inside it. I was touched by the matter of fact way in which the story was told, not only because of the bad times our young protagonist goes through, but also because of the way in which he decides to thank every single person that helped him along the way.<br /><br />The writing itself would have benefited from a more exhaustive editing work. Even though the language is very good, the long sentences and unending lists make the reader lose the trail sometimes.</span>
