        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2094945390?book_show_action=true">Sep 04, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Melanie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Melanie" href="/user/show/7861708-melanie">Melanie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/11244523-solacers">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7861708-melanie?shelf=mels-shelf">mels-shelf</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2094945390" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2258634948360112846">I can never figure out how to write a review without being a spoiler. True, this book pulled me though to the end. True, it tugged at my heart strings. Also true that I had some problems with the connecting, then disconnecting of some of the main characters in this book. I found some behaviors just so bad. But it is another culture, and it did help me understand that.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


